metadata.name: Room from 1997 #45
metadata.description:
Step into a time capsule with this unique NFT, transporting you back to a stylish room straight out of 1997. Every detail has been carefully crafted to create an immersive experience, complete with interactive electronic devices.

Take a seat on the plush couch and start exploring the room. Turn on the TV and VHS player to watch classic movies, or fire up the computer to surf the internet with a slow-but-steady modem connection. Don't forget to turn on the power strip to activate all of the devices, just like in the good old days.

As you look around the room, you'll notice that each variation offers a different color scheme for the walls and floors, as well as a unique selection of furniture. The AI-generated images on the TV and computer screens are also randomized, adding to the nostalgia-inducing experience.

Hover your mouse cursor over any electronic device buttons and watch as it lights up and responds to your touch. You'll feel like you're really in the room, controlling every aspect of the technology around you.

Overall, this NFT offers a one-of-a-kind trip back in time, complete with all the quirks and nuances of the technology of the era. It's a must-have for anyone who loves the 90s aesthetic and wants to relive the magic of that era.

metadata.name: Impressions of Order #82
metadata.description:
‘Impressions of Order’ is a collection of 300 generative compositions. 

Inspired by 90s ROM cartridges, server farms and future cityscapes this project explores perception and documentation of ‘order’ within complex systems. 

--------------------------------------------------------

This artwork is best enjoyed in high-resolution so that the subtle layering, colour shifts, variation in hard and soft edges, faint impressions of construction, and the various low-probability glitchy events can be fully appreciated. 

By default, the artwork will load in 2K resolution (1400 x 2000 px). It is recommended that you view the work in 4K or 6K to appreciate the finer details. 

The keyboard buttons: “2”, “4”, and “6” can be pressed to change the resolution to 2K, 4K and 6K resolution accordingly. 

To download an image at its current resolution, press the keyboard button “S”.

--------------------------------------------------------

Artwork created with p5.js

@nbswwit
Sept 2022

metadata.name: The Fire Within #84
metadata.description:
This project is a study of ink, everything is generated in code without using any texture. 
It is an attempt to capture the ink bleeding effect and the look of the traditional Chinese paintings that have texts on top with modern approaches.

metadata.name: Esplorazione #2
metadata.description:
Exploration can be seen as a fundamental aspect of human nature, as it drives us to seek out new knowledge, experiences, and understanding of the world around us. It is a never-ending quest for truth, for understanding the unknown and the mysterious.

Philosophically, exploration can be seen as a means of self-discovery and self-actualization. By venturing into the unknown, we are forced to confront our own limitations, biases and assumptions. We are also presented with new perspectives and ways of understanding, which can challenge and broaden our own understanding of the world and ourselves.

Exploration can be seen as a form of self-expression and artistic creativity. It allows us to test the boundaries of what is possible, to push the limits of what we know, and to discover new and innovative ways of seeing the world.

It can be understood as a fundamental aspect of human existence, one that allows us to transcend our individual selves and to connect with the greater world around us. It is a never-ending quest for truth, for understanding the unknown and the mysterious, and for discovering our own place in the world.

Press [s] to download the canvas in original resolution.

metadata.name: Focal Point #11
metadata.description:
The "Focal Point" series showcases a unique combination of four square artworks arranged in the shape of a plus sign on a textured brown paper. The central motif present in each artwork is an anchor, which also serves as the basis for the color palette throughout the series. The artist began by digitally creating a precisionist central artwork which led to further creation of 28 total artworks, divided into four sets, each set representing a direction.

The symmetry of the resulting form is striking, with the four squares perfectly aligning to create a cohesive and balanced composition. The use of textured brown paper as the background adds depth and dimension to the series, creating an interesting contrast with the clean lines and geometric shapes of the artworks.

The series is an exploration of unity and balance, using the plus sign, a symbol of addition, congruence and equilibrium, to visually represent the idea that by bringing different elements together, a new and harmonious whole can be formed. 

The artist's intent is to convey that despite our differences in physical and intellectual attributes, we are all the same at our core. 

20% of the proceeds from this project will be donated to Southern Exposure, an artist-centered non-profit organization committed to supporting visual artists, that has been in the San Francisco Bay Area since 1974.

For more information regarding my past and upcoming projects, please visit meditationsincolor.com.

metadata.name: WatSplash #4
metadata.description:
Water Splash is a stunning piece of art that captures the beauty and "movement" of watercolors, the piece features multiple drops of watercolors as it falls from a "faucet" and creates a splash upon impact. The bright colors and bold brushstrokes used in the painting add to its dynamism and energy.

Overall, Water Splash is a breathtaking work of art that is sure to impress and inspire.

I hope you enjoy it!
